messages.content:
THOUGHT: The verifier crash arises when reshuffling insertelement chains across different basic blocks, leading to dominance violations. A conservative fix is to skip the reshuffle when the insertelement instructions belong to multiple different parent blocks. I will insert a guard that checks parents of all insertelements in a group, and if they differ, continue without performing the reshuffle for that group. This avoids creating shuffles that don't dominate all uses and should prevent the crash.

```bash
python3 - << 'PY'
import sys
p='llvm/lib/Transforms/Vectorize/SLPVectorizer.cpp'
s=open(p).read()
anchor = "    InsertElementInst *FirstInsert = ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements.front();\n    InsertElementInst *LastInsert = ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements.back();\n"
ins = """    // Guard: if insertelements are in different parent blocks, skip reshuffling to avoid dominance issues.
    SmallPtrSet<BasicBlock *, 4> Parents;
    for (InsertElementInst *IEP : ShuffledInserts[I].InsertElements)
      Parents.insert(IEP->getParent());
    if (Parents.size() > 1)
      continue;
"""
if anchor in s:
    s = s.replace(anchor, anchor + ins)
    open(p,'w').write(s)
    print('Inserted multi-parent guard to skip reshuffle')
else:
    print('Anchor not found', file=sys.stderr)
PY
&& submit-patch
```

